summary:
My personal settings for the FXAA Post Process Injector mod.
It took a while to get it how I wanted, so I figure I might as well as share.
descriptionHtml:
Goals I had in mind:

- Make it sharper without screwing up stars and other small objects 
- Make it more saturated and lively, but not too much
- Use the Sepia filter to make the game \"warmer\" so it\'s not as grey/blue as the default look
- Make nights darker 

NOTE: This is just the settings file, you need to first download the FXAA Injector mod by some_dude here:
http://www.skyrimnexus.com/downloads/file.php?id=131

INSTALL:
1. Backup your injFX_Settings.h file and your injFX_Shaders folder before doing anything
2. Extract the contents to your Skyrim folder and overwrite when prompted
author: Ultros
